# =============================================================================
# Densiometry — whitelist .gitignore
#
# This repo tracks only source code and densitometry INPUT data (.SCN raw
# scans + .DAT operator-edited references).  The source trial folders are a
# multi-GB mix of images, zips, databases and raw scanner intermediates that
# must never enter git, so we ignore everything by default and re-allow only
# the file types we want.  `git add .` over a copied trial tree then picks up
# just the .SCN/.DAT pairs and scripts.
# =============================================================================

# Ignore everything...
*

# ...but descend into directories so nested files can be re-included
!*/

# Repo metadata & docs
!.gitignore
!*.md

# Source code
!*.R

# Densitometry data (raw scans + edited references; both letter cases)
!*.SCN
!*.scn
!*.DAT
!*.dat

# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Still exclude generated pipeline output and R session artefacts, even though
# some would otherwise match the rules above.
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
output/
Rplots.pdf
.Rhistory
.RData
.Rproj.user/
